WEBVTT

00:01.160 --> 00:11.040
♪♪

00:11.080 --> 00:21.040
♪♪

00:21.080 --> 00:31.000
♪♪

00:31.040 --> 00:41.000
♪♪

00:41.040 --> 00:45.960
[Film projector clicking]

00:46.000 --> 00:49.000
[Cellphone ringing]

00:52.360 --> 00:55.600
[Clattering]

00:55.640 --> 00:58.080
[Ringing continues]

00:58.120 --> 00:59.800
♪♪

00:59.840 --> 01:00.960
[Ringing stops]

01:01.000 --> 01:02.880
Hello?

01:02.920 --> 01:05.520
Yes. I'm -- I'm awake.

01:05.560 --> 01:09.240
♪♪

01:09.280 --> 01:12.200
Yeah.

01:12.240 --> 01:14.040
Yeah, I know Mrs. Graham.

01:14.080 --> 01:16.880
Uh, yeah, we did.

01:16.920 --> 01:18.760
♪♪

01:18.800 --> 01:21.040
Yes, when I was at Defoe's.

01:21.080 --> 01:23.920
♪♪

01:23.960 --> 01:25.560
[Switch clicks]

01:25.600 --> 01:26.800
No.

01:26.840 --> 01:28.640
No. Who's Indiana Ray?

01:28.680 --> 01:35.760
♪♪

01:35.800 --> 01:42.840
♪♪

01:42.880 --> 01:49.960
♪♪

01:50.000 --> 01:52.360
Ramsey Sawyer,
Director of Communications
for the Government.

01:52.400 --> 01:54.400
I'm looking after
Mrs. Graham.

01:54.440 --> 01:56.360
We got the heads-up,
thanks to intelligence,

01:56.400 --> 01:58.800
that the Indiana Raysite
has been hacked.

01:58.840 --> 02:01.120
The leaked client list
will go online at 7:00 a.m.,

02:01.160 --> 02:03.400
which slightly blows
their tagline as the place to go

02:03.440 --> 02:05.800
for the discreet
extramarital affair.

02:05.840 --> 02:07.240
Mr. Graham
is on the list,

02:07.280 --> 02:08.960
and we have the Chinese
president and his wife

02:09.000 --> 02:12.560
arriving for a high-profile
state visit later today.

02:12.600 --> 02:15.640
As Foreign Secretary,
Mrs. Graham will be hosting.

02:15.680 --> 02:17.680
This will hijack
the entire trip.

02:17.720 --> 02:20.400
[Door opens]PM's looking for
damage limitation.

02:20.440 --> 02:23.080
Mrs. Graham, however,
has other ideas.

02:23.120 --> 02:24.840
[Door closes]

02:24.880 --> 02:28.120
♪♪

02:28.160 --> 02:30.760
Mrs. Graham.
Hannah Stern.

02:30.800 --> 02:32.400
We met briefly
when I was at Defoe's.

02:32.440 --> 02:33.440
[Cellphone dings]

02:33.480 --> 02:35.880
-Bill.
-Mr. Graham. Yes.

02:35.920 --> 02:38.160
Darling, what are you doing up?
Go back to bed.

02:40.320 --> 02:43.000
Aye, Dad's with me.

02:43.040 --> 02:45.400
We'll explain
when we're home.

02:45.440 --> 02:47.280
No, Nanna's there.

02:47.320 --> 02:49.240
Yeah.

02:49.280 --> 02:51.520
He's here.

02:51.560 --> 02:52.720
Yeah.

02:55.240 --> 02:57.200
Alright,
little man?

02:57.240 --> 03:00.640
No, don't wake Tommy and Gabe.
Let them sleep.

03:00.680 --> 03:01.920
We'll be home soon.

03:01.960 --> 03:04.280
[Clock ticking]

03:04.320 --> 03:06.080
You all right, darling?
Would you like a diazepam?

03:06.120 --> 03:08.320
No, I want
a bloody divorce!

03:10.600 --> 03:12.480
Ramsey: We do need to get
some kind of statement out.

03:12.520 --> 03:13.760
The press will be
scrabbling for copy

03:13.800 --> 03:15.360
as soon as the list
goes online.

03:15.400 --> 03:17.480
It's a blanket statement, just
something to keep them at bay

03:17.520 --> 03:20.160
while we -- youdecide
on your next move.

03:20.200 --> 03:22.480
[Clears throat]

03:22.520 --> 03:25.920
"Respect our privacy
whilst we rebuild our marriage."

03:25.960 --> 03:27.160
I won't say "rebuild."

03:28.600 --> 03:29.920
How about "review"?

03:29.960 --> 03:31.520
Yeah, good -- "review."

03:31.560 --> 03:33.080
"Review's"
a little open-ended.

03:33.120 --> 03:34.400
Well, I thought
I was being generous.

03:34.440 --> 03:36.280
-It was a few meetings.
-Meetings?!

03:36.320 --> 03:38.200
Emma, please.
Can we talk about this later?

03:38.240 --> 03:40.560
How many times?

03:40.600 --> 03:42.440
The same woman?

03:42.480 --> 03:43.760
Different women?

03:45.040 --> 03:46.320
A number of women.

03:46.360 --> 03:48.320
I met one in particular
several times.

03:48.360 --> 03:50.080
[Sighs]

03:50.120 --> 03:52.720
It...was a connection.

03:54.800 --> 03:56.200
I'm sorry.

03:56.240 --> 03:57.640
I am so sorry.

03:57.680 --> 04:00.960
Did she spank you
or did you spank her?

04:01.000 --> 04:03.960
[Ticking continues]

04:04.000 --> 04:06.640
I will contest it, Emma,
if you ask for a divorce.

04:06.680 --> 04:09.800
I will contest it.
We are a family.

04:09.840 --> 04:11.240
Whatever you think
of my behavior --

04:11.280 --> 04:14.840
and I'm not proud of it --
think of our boys.

04:14.880 --> 04:16.480
We are a family.

04:16.520 --> 04:19.280
You didn't think of family
when you went on that site.

04:19.320 --> 04:22.120
[Ticking continues]

04:24.800 --> 04:27.600
[Door opens]If I could speak
to Mrs. Graham?

04:30.000 --> 04:31.640
Alone, please?

04:31.680 --> 04:33.440
The PM wants to see you
in half an hour.

04:33.480 --> 04:35.920
Oh, I bet
she bloody does.

04:35.960 --> 04:37.280
[Clears throat]

04:39.040 --> 04:41.360
[Doors close]

04:41.400 --> 04:44.040
[Ticking continues]

04:47.280 --> 04:48.920
I haven't even
brushed my teeth.

04:48.960 --> 04:50.440
[Chuckles lightly]

04:54.360 --> 04:56.360
He used his own name,
for Christ's sake.

04:56.400 --> 04:58.800
First rule of security --
if you're staying in a hotel,

04:58.840 --> 05:00.640
you're booking a car,
use a different name.

05:00.680 --> 05:01.960
It's basic.

05:03.360 --> 05:06.280
Mrs. Graham,
I'm curious.

05:06.320 --> 05:09.360
I no longer work
with Defoe's.

05:09.400 --> 05:11.120
You usually
use my mother --

05:11.160 --> 05:13.120
And now I want
to use you.

05:13.160 --> 05:17.080
[Ticking continues]

05:17.120 --> 05:18.840
Okay.

05:18.880 --> 05:24.760
♪♪

05:24.800 --> 05:27.760
So, let me, uh, talk you through
what that might look like.

05:27.800 --> 05:28.920
Mm-hmm.

05:28.960 --> 05:31.040
♪♪

05:31.080 --> 05:34.560
Divorce is a process of
redrawing all the boundaries.

05:34.600 --> 05:38.200
Emotionally, psychologically,
economically.

05:38.240 --> 05:41.040
I've heard it described
as open-heart surgery

05:41.080 --> 05:42.320
whilst you're still awake.

05:42.360 --> 05:44.760
With no reassurances

05:44.800 --> 05:48.640
that everything will be
put back in the right place.

05:48.680 --> 05:50.920
I am not saying this
to alarm you,

05:50.960 --> 05:52.720
but I want you
to be clear.

05:52.760 --> 05:54.960
♪♪

05:55.000 --> 05:58.360
Leaving any marriage
is frightening.

05:58.400 --> 06:00.160
You've built a life
around a person,

06:00.200 --> 06:03.080
and when that breaks down --I'm not frightened
of leaving.

06:03.120 --> 06:05.840
It's staying that
I can't stomach any--

06:05.880 --> 06:08.680
[Sobs]

06:08.720 --> 06:10.480
It's the lies.

06:10.520 --> 06:12.120
♪♪

06:12.160 --> 06:15.800
I mean, who the hell
is Indiana Ray, anyway?

06:15.840 --> 06:17.440
♪♪

06:17.480 --> 06:19.720
[Sobs]

06:21.560 --> 06:23.240
Pull in Nigel.

06:23.280 --> 06:25.960
Ask Ann and Michael
to set up calls.

06:26.000 --> 06:27.200
I'm just coming in.

06:27.240 --> 06:29.360
[Snoring softly]

06:29.400 --> 06:31.240
♪♪

06:31.280 --> 06:32.400
Tell Nina --

06:32.440 --> 06:35.200
Not in yet
or picking up her phone.

06:35.240 --> 06:38.240
I've tried her flat
and left four messages.[Telephone ringing]

06:38.280 --> 06:39.520
Do you want me
to try again?

06:39.560 --> 06:40.840
Yes.

06:40.880 --> 06:42.600
Clear my diary
for the morning.

06:42.640 --> 06:45.840
I want the entire building
ready and online.

06:45.880 --> 06:48.400
Bill Graham's on the list.

06:48.440 --> 06:49.480
Put in a call.

06:49.520 --> 06:51.440
Already have.

06:51.480 --> 06:53.440
Emma's gone with Hannah.

06:53.480 --> 06:56.120
[Door closes]Don't. It's off.

06:56.160 --> 06:57.920
I'm on my way.

06:57.960 --> 07:01.040
[Carton thuds]

07:01.080 --> 07:02.560
You're still
angry with me.

07:02.600 --> 07:03.960
Why would I
be angry with you?

07:04.000 --> 07:05.680
Rose, please.

07:08.000 --> 07:09.920
-Don't!
-Don't!

07:09.960 --> 07:13.160
Okay. I am stepping away
from the milk.

07:13.200 --> 07:14.960
See you later.

07:15.000 --> 07:16.960
My parents are
looking forward to tomorrow.

07:17.000 --> 07:19.160
They asked if there was
anything they could bring.

07:21.640 --> 07:25.120
-[Snorts]
-At the supper after the church?

07:25.160 --> 07:27.040
You finally get to meet?

07:27.080 --> 07:29.400
-I didn't forget.
-You forgot.

07:31.240 --> 07:33.520
[Sniffs]

07:34.960 --> 07:37.120
Rose.
We had a father
who wanted to see us.

07:37.160 --> 07:38.520
[Door opens, closes]

07:38.560 --> 07:41.160
And if you say
you did it for us...

07:41.200 --> 07:44.400
[Cellphone ringing]

07:44.440 --> 07:47.160
I'm --

07:47.200 --> 07:49.800
Bye.

07:49.840 --> 07:52.120
[Coffee machine spurting,
footsteps fading]

07:52.160 --> 07:53.120
Oh, shit.

07:53.160 --> 07:55.400
[Camera shutters clicking]

07:55.440 --> 07:58.040
Reporter: The extramarital
dating siteIndiana Ray

07:58.080 --> 07:59.680
has been hacked.

07:59.720 --> 08:02.320
50,000 client names
have been released online,

08:02.360 --> 08:05.120
including the husband
of the Foreign Secretary.

08:05.160 --> 08:07.400
As Mrs. Graham is hosting
the Chinese president

08:07.440 --> 08:09.160
and his wife
on their high-profile

08:09.200 --> 08:12.040
state visit later today,
this news could not have come

08:12.080 --> 08:13.560
at a worse time
for the government.

08:13.600 --> 08:15.640
[Paper shuffling,
telephones ringing]

08:15.680 --> 08:17.720
[Indistinct talking]

08:17.760 --> 08:19.400
-Hey.
-Hey.

08:19.440 --> 08:21.560
So, how many names
are we talking about?

08:21.600 --> 08:24.000
50,000 leaked
one hour ago online.

08:24.040 --> 08:27.000
Possible threat of another
50,000 over the next 48 hours.

08:27.040 --> 08:29.480
Some far-right Christian group
trying to bring the site down.

08:29.520 --> 08:31.240
Martin Charleston.

08:31.280 --> 08:33.720
-What, theMartin Charleston?
-First out of the gate.

08:33.760 --> 08:35.160
The press have started
to pick up on names.

08:35.200 --> 08:37.880
And the paps are just
swarming downstairs.[Thud]

08:37.920 --> 08:40.560
David Tyle,
Sir Ron Massey.

08:40.600 --> 08:42.560
-We did his last prenup.
-Lucky for him.

08:42.600 --> 08:44.160
Tell clients we can
talk to them on Skype.

08:44.200 --> 08:46.960
J.J. Johnson called in
their lawyers at 5:00 a.m.

08:47.000 --> 08:48.320
Find out how
they got the heads-up.

08:48.360 --> 08:50.160
Next list comes in,
I want first pick.

08:50.200 --> 08:51.520
Any interesting calls
come in yet?

08:51.560 --> 08:54.520
Actually...Emma Graham.

08:54.560 --> 08:56.840
As in the Right Honorable
Emma Graham?

08:56.880 --> 08:58.440
I got the call
at 4:00 a.m.

08:58.480 --> 09:00.480
She wants a divorce.
He's threatening to contest it.

09:00.520 --> 09:02.040
Brilliant.
Double the hours in court.

09:02.080 --> 09:03.880
This could run and run.
A letter of engagement?

09:03.920 --> 09:05.440
On its way back
and signed.

09:05.480 --> 09:07.360
Your mother's
going to be, uhh --Yes, she is.

09:07.400 --> 09:10.400
[Knock on door]Press statement's in.

09:10.440 --> 09:12.640
"Foreign Secretary
reviews marriage

09:12.680 --> 09:14.400
in wake
of Indiana Rayleak."

09:14.440 --> 09:16.280
And the moral
of the tale is,

09:16.320 --> 09:18.880
the best affairs
are the ones you never had.

09:20.800 --> 09:22.240
Zander: Okay, okay!

09:22.280 --> 09:26.560
Ladies and gentlemen,
welcome to Divorce D-Day.

09:26.600 --> 09:28.600
Any plans tonight -- cancel.

09:28.640 --> 09:29.680
Over to you.

09:29.720 --> 09:32.640
Jason. Martin.

09:32.680 --> 09:35.000
Here you go. Becca.
If you can distribute these.

09:35.040 --> 09:38.560
Okay, guys, we're breaking the
list down into blocks of 500.

09:38.600 --> 09:40.800
Johnny T., Johnny A.,
I'm putting you both
on Ryder Nelson.

09:40.840 --> 09:42.400
Call just came in.
I know. I know.

09:42.440 --> 09:44.080
He's a nightmare,
but he pays up front.

09:44.120 --> 09:45.480
Maggie, Sean,

09:45.520 --> 09:47.160
we've got a number of calls
from new clients.

09:47.200 --> 09:48.960
Please follow up on those,
yeah?

09:49.000 --> 09:53.400
And the rest, any names you
recognize, ring and call, okay?

09:53.440 --> 09:55.080
Two days of the year
when none of you sleep?

09:55.120 --> 09:56.960
First working Monday
in January

09:57.000 --> 09:59.000
and September,
when the kids have gone back.

09:59.040 --> 10:00.560
And now a third,

10:00.600 --> 10:02.560
forever to be remembered
as Indiana Rayday.

10:02.600 --> 10:03.840
[Laughter]

10:03.880 --> 10:06.040
And, guys, please,
be discreet, okay?

10:06.080 --> 10:07.560
Throughout the day,
we will undoubtedly

10:07.600 --> 10:09.960
be dealing
with high-profile clients.

10:10.000 --> 10:11.800
Press are downstairs,
and they're showing

10:11.840 --> 10:15.240
no signs of moving, so use
the goods lift if needs be.

10:15.280 --> 10:17.960
Zander: Get billing, comrades.
Go, go, go!

10:18.000 --> 10:21.360
[Telephone ringing in distance]

10:21.400 --> 10:25.160
[Footsteps approaching]

10:25.200 --> 10:26.720
[Paper rustling]

10:26.760 --> 10:32.320
♪♪

10:32.360 --> 10:34.800
[Ringing continues]

10:34.840 --> 10:36.400
Ruth: Nina!

10:36.440 --> 10:43.760
♪♪

10:43.800 --> 10:45.200
Nina!!

10:45.240 --> 10:46.880
♪♪

10:46.920 --> 10:50.240
[Indistinct conversations,
telephones ringing]

10:50.280 --> 10:53.400
♪♪

10:53.440 --> 10:55.240
You're late.

10:55.280 --> 10:56.720
I've worked every day
of every week,

10:56.760 --> 10:58.480
including evenings and weekends,
since Hannah left.

10:58.520 --> 11:01.320
And for this, you want
a marching band and
Donna on the kazoo?

11:01.360 --> 11:04.280
No! Not there!
Not there.

11:04.320 --> 11:07.000
Amy, why don't you find
something else to do

11:07.040 --> 11:09.000
while I get her
back in her cage?

11:11.760 --> 11:13.080
[Telephone ringing]

11:13.120 --> 11:16.720
Cut the wisecracks
in front of my staff.

11:16.760 --> 11:19.960
Davey McKenzie,
still paperwork missing.

11:20.000 --> 11:21.840
Go through it with Lola.
All the accounts.

11:21.880 --> 11:23.600
You might be
working late.

11:23.640 --> 11:27.000
-The FDR's not until --
-Just do it, Nina! Please!

11:27.040 --> 11:29.960
We cannot afford
to lose Mr. McKenzie.

11:30.000 --> 11:33.160
Incidentally, can you put in
a call to Mr. Pope?

11:33.200 --> 11:35.080
Remind him
that he still hasn't paid.

11:35.120 --> 11:36.120
Sure.

11:38.240 --> 11:40.400
[Telephones ringing,
indistinct talking in distance]

11:43.240 --> 11:44.920
[Sniffs] Anything else?

11:44.960 --> 11:46.360
Oh, I don't know.

11:46.400 --> 11:47.880
How about this check
Dad sent?

11:47.920 --> 11:49.520
Do you think
it will still clear?

11:51.320 --> 11:53.200
So, are we
going to buy him out?
Nina.

11:53.240 --> 11:54.920
I'm actually
not even talking to you!

11:54.960 --> 11:56.560
For God's sake!
[Slams desk]

11:56.600 --> 11:58.560
♪♪

11:58.600 --> 12:00.440
I understand
that you are all upset,

12:00.480 --> 12:02.800
that there is a conversation
to be had.

12:02.840 --> 12:04.160
Yes, you are correct.

12:04.200 --> 12:06.680
My intention is
to buy your father out.

12:06.720 --> 12:09.320
However, this is a business
and another working day,

12:09.360 --> 12:11.520
so can we please
save this for later

12:11.560 --> 12:13.320
and make hay
while the sun shines?

12:13.360 --> 12:16.120
Because, if you hadn't
noticed, everyone is...

12:16.160 --> 12:17.920
-Yes, I know.
-Everyone is...

12:17.960 --> 12:21.680
-Everyone is divorcing.
-Everyone is divorcing today.

12:21.720 --> 12:24.080
♪♪

12:24.120 --> 12:25.440
God.

12:25.480 --> 12:32.160
♪♪

12:32.200 --> 12:34.600
Thank you.

12:34.640 --> 12:37.320
Thank you.

12:37.360 --> 12:40.080
[Footsteps approaching]

12:40.120 --> 12:43.400
♪♪

12:50.760 --> 12:52.880
[Keys rattling]

12:58.200 --> 13:05.560
♪♪

13:05.600 --> 13:14.120
♪♪

13:15.560 --> 13:18.440
Okay, so, I've been
looking through more
of the McKenzie accounts.

13:18.480 --> 13:21.080
-Mm-hmm.
-Notwithstanding the £18 million

13:21.120 --> 13:23.240
which has been siphoned through
the Daniel Duchy account...

13:23.280 --> 13:25.360
That's a lot of loose change
for a 10-year-old.

13:25.400 --> 13:27.280
Isn't it?

13:27.320 --> 13:30.320
There's still another
£9 million unaccounted for.

13:30.360 --> 13:31.640
Interesting.

13:31.680 --> 13:33.200
As company secretary,

13:33.240 --> 13:37.200
doesn't Goldie have the right
to attend company meetings?

13:37.240 --> 13:40.000
There's a gathering
of the McKenzie board today.

13:40.040 --> 13:41.240
Call her.

13:43.120 --> 13:44.200
[Door opens]

13:44.240 --> 13:46.360
[Telephone ringing in distance]

13:46.400 --> 13:52.680
♪♪

13:52.720 --> 13:54.120
Sorry.

13:54.160 --> 14:02.080
♪♪

14:02.120 --> 14:04.720
[Indistinct talking,
telephone ringing]

14:04.760 --> 14:07.520
♪♪

14:07.560 --> 14:09.720
Hannah.

14:09.760 --> 14:12.440
-Mother.
-I had a lunch nearby.

14:12.480 --> 14:13.680
Have you five minutes?

14:13.720 --> 14:15.280
My office is this way.

14:15.320 --> 14:17.680
[Telephone ringing]

14:17.720 --> 14:20.040
[Indistinct conversation]

14:20.080 --> 14:29.040
♪♪

14:29.080 --> 14:30.800
[Door closes]

14:32.760 --> 14:35.080
Emma Graham --
she's myclient.

14:35.120 --> 14:37.720
First rule --
all bets are off

14:37.760 --> 14:40.240
until the letter of engagement
is signed.

14:45.440 --> 14:47.200
Shall we sit down,
or shall we stand?

14:49.080 --> 14:50.760
Putting aside
the obvious conversation

14:50.800 --> 14:52.320
that we need to have...

14:52.360 --> 14:53.960
Hmm,
that you lied to us.

14:55.800 --> 15:00.960
That we had a father
who wanted to see us.

15:01.000 --> 15:03.360
Forever
three against one.

15:03.400 --> 15:05.560
You need to buy him out.

15:05.600 --> 15:07.160
[Scoffs]

15:07.200 --> 15:09.120
I'll certainly
bear that in mind.

15:09.160 --> 15:11.080
It is in hand, Hannah.

15:12.520 --> 15:16.080
Well, putting all that
aside for a moment --

15:16.120 --> 15:18.040
Emma and Bill Graham,
they have been married

15:18.080 --> 15:19.920
for 27 years.

15:19.960 --> 15:21.880
They have
three adorable boys.

15:21.920 --> 15:23.440
The youngest is still
in primary school.

15:23.480 --> 15:25.040
I can't talk about
ongoing cases.

15:25.080 --> 15:26.120
[Chuckles]

15:26.160 --> 15:27.960
I appreciate
that this must be

15:28.000 --> 15:29.920
a highly original feeling
for you,

15:29.960 --> 15:31.600
taking one of my clients,

15:31.640 --> 15:34.200
but let me bring you
up to speed.

15:34.240 --> 15:36.160
She can't divorce.

15:36.200 --> 15:38.560
No, she can,
and she is going to.

15:38.600 --> 15:41.520
Do you really want
to break that family up?

15:41.560 --> 15:43.760
What,
better to live a lie?

15:45.600 --> 15:47.040
I don't see it
as a lie.

15:47.080 --> 15:49.920
I see it as an economy
with the truth.

15:51.760 --> 15:53.000
And your grandfather
was partial

15:53.040 --> 15:55.240
to the odd bit
of spanking, apparently.

15:55.280 --> 15:58.400
That's way
too much information.

15:58.440 --> 16:00.560
How do you even know?

16:00.600 --> 16:03.960
[Chuckles] Of course.
You know everything.

16:04.000 --> 16:06.960
As ever, this has been
an enlightening meeting,

16:07.000 --> 16:09.280
but I have
a very busy day.

16:09.320 --> 16:12.360
Talking of spanking
and all other things,

16:12.400 --> 16:16.040
Defoe's helped take out
a privacy injunction

16:16.080 --> 16:18.680
for the Grahams
against a national newspaper

16:18.720 --> 16:20.160
five years ago.

16:20.200 --> 16:22.120
One of their journalists
was about to break a story

16:22.160 --> 16:25.760
that Bill had visited a hotel
with a mature lady

16:25.800 --> 16:27.840
and several pieces
of kit.

16:29.320 --> 16:31.440
And you did what?

16:31.480 --> 16:35.240
These were two mutually
consenting adults engaging in --

16:35.280 --> 16:37.000
Which journalist?

16:37.040 --> 16:39.440
-Matthew Royston.
-He's a piranha.

16:39.480 --> 16:43.440
Well, to avoid any details
of that indiscretion coming out,

16:43.480 --> 16:47.560
Emma signed a witness statement
stating that Bill had, in fact,

16:47.600 --> 16:50.640
spent the entire weekend
with her.

16:50.680 --> 16:52.600
-Oh, God. No, no.
-Yeah.

16:52.640 --> 16:56.720
So if this goes to court,
these details may come to light.

16:56.760 --> 16:58.040
You perverted
the course of justice.

16:58.080 --> 17:00.000
And they will come
after Emma.

17:00.040 --> 17:01.680
♪♪

17:01.720 --> 17:03.200
And you.

17:03.240 --> 17:06.040
♪♪

17:06.080 --> 17:08.640
How could you do this?
How could you be so stupid?

17:08.680 --> 17:11.960
I was trying to help a client
save her marriage.

17:12.000 --> 17:14.560
Not to mention the fact
you could be struck off.

17:14.600 --> 17:16.600
Your first duty
is always to the courts.

17:16.640 --> 17:18.960
Oh, thank you -- a fact
that had escaped my attention.

17:19.000 --> 17:21.440
Oh, really, Mother?
You choose sarcasm now?

17:21.480 --> 17:22.480
[Knock on door]

17:25.000 --> 17:27.400
Zander.Twice in one month.

17:27.440 --> 17:30.240
Don't you get vertigo
being up this high?

17:30.280 --> 17:31.960
Oddly, no.

17:32.000 --> 17:34.640
I'll see you
at the church tomorrow.

17:34.680 --> 17:36.000
There's a meeting
of the tribes.

17:36.040 --> 17:37.680
-Oh.
-[Chuckles]

17:37.720 --> 17:39.800
You will be on time?
-Yes, yep.

17:39.840 --> 17:41.720
It's a wonderful thing
about Hannah.

17:41.760 --> 17:44.520
You can always rely on her
to do the right thing.

17:48.920 --> 17:51.000
[Engine humming]

17:51.040 --> 17:54.360
[Indistinct talking]

17:54.400 --> 17:55.760
Goldie?

17:55.800 --> 17:56.760
[Laughs]

17:56.800 --> 17:58.920
You still here, Bobby?

17:58.960 --> 18:00.520
[Chuckles]

18:00.560 --> 18:02.200
They'll have to
wheel me out.

18:02.240 --> 18:04.080
[Laughs]

18:04.120 --> 18:06.080
I'll see you later!

18:10.400 --> 18:12.360
-Mum, what --
-Board meeting.

18:12.400 --> 18:16.640
It's alright, love.
I know where it is.

18:16.680 --> 18:20.440
♪♪

18:20.480 --> 18:21.560
[Telephones ringing]

18:21.600 --> 18:23.600
Mum, please.
I know you're angry.

18:23.640 --> 18:25.760
You have a right to be,
but this isn't the place.

18:25.800 --> 18:29.640
Breathe, Michael.
Don't make a scene.

18:29.680 --> 18:31.560
Mum, don't! Mum!

18:31.600 --> 18:33.080
Overall, we're looking --

18:33.120 --> 18:35.360
♪♪

18:35.400 --> 18:39.640
...at a flotation figure
of £148 million,

18:39.680 --> 18:43.520
[Door closes]with a healthy
shareholder's net profit

18:43.560 --> 18:46.800
of close to 42p
in every pound.

18:46.840 --> 18:49.120
And you can substantiate
that figure?

18:49.160 --> 18:52.240
♪♪

18:52.280 --> 18:55.960
If you'd like to look
at your shareholders report,

18:56.000 --> 18:58.360
uh, page...

18:58.400 --> 19:00.600
page...12,Can I see that?

19:00.640 --> 19:03.200
I can talk you
through the exact figures.

19:03.240 --> 19:08.000
♪♪

19:08.040 --> 19:10.720
[Telephones ringing]

19:10.760 --> 19:14.520
[Indistinct talking]

19:14.560 --> 19:16.160
What the hell
are you playing at?

19:16.200 --> 19:18.280
As company secretary,
it's important I keep abreast--

19:18.320 --> 19:19.960
[Pounds wall]

19:20.000 --> 19:22.200
You see a man
who can lie about a child?

19:22.240 --> 19:23.760
What else
are you lying about?

19:23.800 --> 19:27.160
-You're sleepwalking, love.
-Well, I'm awake now.

19:27.200 --> 19:29.400
And I'm onto you, Davey.

19:31.880 --> 19:34.120
See you in court.

19:34.160 --> 19:37.120
You go down that road, it won't
just be me you're hurting.

19:37.160 --> 19:39.120
[Indistinct talking]

19:44.160 --> 19:48.680
♪♪

19:48.720 --> 19:50.840
[Pen clicking]

19:50.880 --> 19:54.840
♪♪

19:54.880 --> 19:58.720
[Paper rustling]

19:58.760 --> 20:00.560
[Sighs]

20:00.600 --> 20:02.800
♪♪

20:02.840 --> 20:06.120
[Telephones ringing in distance]

20:06.160 --> 20:08.360
[Pen thuds]

20:08.400 --> 20:10.400
[Indistinct conversation]

20:10.440 --> 20:20.040
♪♪

20:20.080 --> 20:23.080
[Knock on door]

20:23.120 --> 20:24.680
-Hi.
-Hi.

20:27.040 --> 20:28.760
That 4:00 a.m.
start kicking in?

20:28.800 --> 20:30.040
Yeah.
Yeah.[Telephone rings]

20:30.080 --> 20:31.160
Oh. It's --

20:31.200 --> 20:33.560
And the West Coast
just woke up.

20:33.600 --> 20:36.600
[Ringing stops, door closes]

20:36.640 --> 20:38.440
[Sighs]

20:38.480 --> 20:41.280
Emma Graham.

20:41.320 --> 20:43.440
They've been together
a long time.

20:45.520 --> 20:47.560
And?

20:47.600 --> 20:49.680
Well, I didn't, umm...

20:49.720 --> 20:51.720
fully walk her through
the consequences.

20:51.760 --> 20:53.640
We're talking about
a high-profile divorce.

20:53.680 --> 20:54.960
Which we do all the time.

20:55.000 --> 20:57.200
[Chuckles]
We're not bloody whores.

20:57.240 --> 20:58.640
[Chuckles]
We're not press-hungry.

20:58.680 --> 20:59.920
We're not like
those other firms.

20:59.960 --> 21:01.600
Yes, we are -- sometimes.

21:01.640 --> 21:03.760
Often. Mainly Zander.

21:03.800 --> 21:05.840
She wants a divorce.

21:05.880 --> 21:08.160
Or she just thinks
she wants a divorce.

21:08.200 --> 21:11.720
It came as a shock.
It was left of field.

21:11.760 --> 21:13.080
She's under
acute pressure.

21:13.120 --> 21:16.280
And you've been up
since 4:00 a.m.

21:16.320 --> 21:17.680
You're tired.

21:17.720 --> 21:21.560
Uhh, I'm going to advise her
to just hold off.

21:21.600 --> 21:23.080
Oh, oh, oh,
wait, wait, wait, wait.

21:23.120 --> 21:24.280
It's a long marriage.

21:24.320 --> 21:25.960
It has its stresses
and strains,

21:26.000 --> 21:28.160
and a-at some point,
both --

21:28.200 --> 21:30.560
[Chuckles]
or one wants to get out.

21:30.600 --> 21:32.240
But they don't.
They stay.

21:32.280 --> 21:33.280
Why?

21:33.320 --> 21:35.200
[Sighs]

21:35.240 --> 21:40.920
Uh, uh, f-for the children
o-or for, um, financial reasons.

21:40.960 --> 21:44.360
Because it's expensive.
We makeit expensive.

21:44.400 --> 21:47.560
-Yeah.
-She has a career, a reputation.

21:47.600 --> 21:49.960
A-A-And maybe it still
works sometimes.

21:50.000 --> 21:53.000
In all its dysfunction,
maybe sometimes they're happy.

21:53.040 --> 21:55.960
Or maybe they're just
too terrified to leave.

21:56.000 --> 21:58.160
So they stay.

21:58.200 --> 22:00.200
And maybe sometimes,
maybe forever,

22:00.240 --> 22:02.840
they're thinking --
no, wishing

22:02.880 --> 22:05.080
that they were
with someone else.

22:05.120 --> 22:09.000
Is that really
what you want for her?

22:09.040 --> 22:11.200
[Chuckles] That's...

22:11.240 --> 22:12.280
What's going on?

22:16.080 --> 22:18.160
The Grahams took out
a privacy injunction

22:18.200 --> 22:20.760
on a newspaper
five years ago.

22:20.800 --> 22:24.680
In that injunction,
Emma lied to protect Bill.

22:29.160 --> 22:31.800
And my mother
helped them do it.

22:31.840 --> 22:33.520
Oh, shit.

22:33.560 --> 22:35.000
[Sighs]

22:36.640 --> 22:39.880
-I shouldn't have told you.
-Yes, you should have.

22:39.920 --> 22:42.760
Okay.
Okay, which newspaper?

22:42.800 --> 22:44.760
Matthew Royston,
The Mail.

22:44.800 --> 22:46.600
I did his last divorce.
I'll call him.

22:47.920 --> 22:49.120
I don't want you involved.

22:49.160 --> 22:50.640
Too bad.

22:50.680 --> 22:52.880
You may need
to advise her to stay.

22:52.920 --> 22:54.720
You don't need
to do this.

23:01.320 --> 23:05.000
You sit tight tonight.
Do nothing.

23:05.040 --> 23:06.840
I'll see
what I can do.

23:09.520 --> 23:10.720
Thank you.

23:12.360 --> 23:13.640
I owe you.

23:14.920 --> 23:17.480
Yeah.
I'll make you pay.

23:21.280 --> 23:23.320
[Telephone ringing in distance]

23:23.360 --> 23:24.560
[Sighs]

23:36.160 --> 23:37.520
You know, tomorrow --

23:37.560 --> 23:39.160
I don't want children.

23:39.200 --> 23:41.240
[Sniffs]

23:41.280 --> 23:43.440
Not now, no,
but we agreed...

23:43.480 --> 23:45.400
-Never.
-...in a few years.

23:45.440 --> 23:47.640
I don't want
children ever.

23:47.680 --> 23:50.080
I mean, there are
too many children in the world.

23:50.120 --> 23:52.600
Like, there a lot, billions.
Like, why add to them?

23:52.640 --> 23:54.000
Kids are the things
that bind you.

23:54.040 --> 23:56.680
No. Not always.

23:56.720 --> 23:58.600
There can be other things.

24:01.440 --> 24:03.640
[Sighs]

24:03.680 --> 24:06.800
[Bell dings]

24:06.840 --> 24:10.080
You're spinning out.
-I need to get off.

24:10.120 --> 24:12.080
[Brakes screeching]

24:14.080 --> 24:16.040
Rose!

24:16.080 --> 24:17.840
[Wind rustling]

24:17.880 --> 24:18.840
Rose!

24:21.400 --> 24:22.400
Rose!

24:25.200 --> 24:26.840
[Breathing heavily]

24:26.880 --> 24:30.280
[Birds chirping,
children playing in distance]

24:30.320 --> 24:32.240
[Sighs]

24:32.280 --> 24:33.880
Sorry.

24:37.840 --> 24:39.720
In China, there's
this, uh, place

24:39.760 --> 24:42.600
where -- where women
never marry.

24:42.640 --> 24:45.640
They just have men drop
through a hole in their bedroom

24:45.680 --> 24:48.240
on a kind of fishhook.

24:48.280 --> 24:51.280
Okay,
you're losing me now.

24:51.320 --> 24:54.600
Stop thinking
about forever.

24:54.640 --> 24:56.840
We're getting married.

24:56.880 --> 24:59.480
Until we don't want
to be married anymore,

24:59.520 --> 25:02.120
and then
we won't be married.

25:02.160 --> 25:04.160
If it's horrible,
then we get out.

25:06.600 --> 25:09.520
♪♪

25:09.560 --> 25:14.120
Okay, let's just -- let's --
let's just live together.

25:14.160 --> 25:16.800
I don't know why.

25:16.840 --> 25:20.360
It means something to me.

25:20.400 --> 25:24.520
Being married to you...

25:24.560 --> 25:27.240
you know,
it matters to me.

25:27.280 --> 25:34.640
♪♪

25:34.680 --> 25:38.920
♪♪

25:38.960 --> 25:41.680
[Sniffs]
I still don't want children.

25:41.720 --> 25:44.200
♪♪

25:44.240 --> 25:45.720
So I'll have to have them
with my next wife.

25:45.760 --> 25:47.800
[Chuckles]

25:47.840 --> 25:49.800
[Laughs]

25:49.840 --> 25:54.320
♪♪

25:57.920 --> 25:59.960
[Cellphone ringing]

26:02.440 --> 26:04.480
[Ringing stops]

26:04.520 --> 26:05.480
Liv.

26:05.520 --> 26:07.800
Liv:
[Voice breaking] Mum.

26:07.840 --> 26:09.840
[Door slams, keys jangle]

26:09.880 --> 26:14.400
♪ Until you realize
that you should go, oh ♪

26:14.440 --> 26:16.440
I'm gonna kill him.

26:16.480 --> 26:17.520
Uhh...

26:17.560 --> 26:19.680
♪ ...seem as old as your omens

26:19.720 --> 26:21.080
Never grow up.

26:21.120 --> 26:23.080
Impossible.
Mm.

26:23.120 --> 26:25.680
♪ ...keep your proud head
from falling ♪[Footsteps ascending]

26:25.720 --> 26:27.160
She's upstairs.

26:27.200 --> 26:29.280
♪ The way is long,
but you can make it ♪

26:29.320 --> 26:31.680
[Glass rattles]♪ Easy on me

26:31.720 --> 26:33.320
♪ And the mother we share

26:33.360 --> 26:37.320
♪ Will never keep our cold heart
from calling ♪

26:37.360 --> 26:39.600
♪ In the dying light

26:39.640 --> 26:41.320
[Door closes]

26:41.360 --> 26:43.960
[Music blaring on headphones]

26:44.000 --> 26:52.320
♪♪

26:52.360 --> 26:55.360
[Music stops]

26:55.400 --> 26:57.000
It's the worst.

27:07.400 --> 27:11.640
I can't say anything to
make it feel better right now.

27:11.680 --> 27:14.440
[Sniffles]

27:14.480 --> 27:17.480
Except
you're beautiful...

27:19.760 --> 27:22.600
...and clever, special.

27:25.800 --> 27:27.560
And he will
kick himself.

27:27.600 --> 27:33.520
♪♪

27:33.560 --> 27:37.280
When it stops feeling bad,
then you'll feel better.

27:37.320 --> 27:40.280
♪♪

27:40.320 --> 27:43.560
And one day, you'll meet
someone else, and --

27:43.600 --> 27:45.920
And he'll screw me over
again.

27:45.960 --> 27:50.360
♪♪

27:50.400 --> 27:53.240
Or he'll be the one that
makes sense of everything.

27:53.280 --> 27:55.760
♪♪

27:55.800 --> 27:57.920
Who sees who you are.

27:57.960 --> 27:59.680
Who you really are.

27:59.720 --> 28:01.560
[Chuckles lightly]

28:01.600 --> 28:03.320
Like you and Dad.

28:03.360 --> 28:07.560
♪♪

28:07.600 --> 28:08.600
Yeah.

28:08.640 --> 28:10.320
♪♪

28:10.360 --> 28:11.480
[Sighs]

28:11.520 --> 28:13.280
Like me and Dad.

28:13.320 --> 28:21.000
♪♪

28:21.040 --> 28:26.280
♪♪

28:26.320 --> 28:27.360
Nice.

28:27.400 --> 28:29.360
♪♪

28:29.400 --> 28:32.440
He can't even spell.
-[Chuckles]

28:32.480 --> 28:35.080
[Sobs]

28:35.120 --> 28:38.480
♪♪

28:38.520 --> 28:41.080
[Indistinct conversation]

28:41.120 --> 28:49.160
♪♪

28:49.200 --> 28:51.320
[Sighs]

28:51.360 --> 29:00.240
♪♪

29:00.280 --> 29:09.120
♪♪

29:09.160 --> 29:11.280
[Line ringing]

29:11.320 --> 29:12.880
♪♪

29:12.920 --> 29:14.560
[Line clicks]Rex?

29:14.600 --> 29:16.640
Finally, she calls.

29:16.680 --> 29:18.680
Well, needs must.

29:18.720 --> 29:21.360
Your payment's late,
Mr. Pope.

29:21.400 --> 29:22.960
At work, then?Man: Rex Pope!

29:23.000 --> 29:24.600
[Cheers and applause]

29:24.640 --> 29:27.200
I may need
to charge you interest.

29:27.240 --> 29:28.680
And...

29:28.720 --> 29:30.400
[Cheers and applause]

29:30.440 --> 29:33.640
[Indistinct talking]

29:33.680 --> 29:36.280
-Night!
-Good night.

29:36.320 --> 29:37.880
A couple of punch lines
over there, so...

29:37.920 --> 29:39.800
♪♪

29:39.840 --> 29:43.480
-He breaks up with her by text.
-Mm.

29:43.520 --> 29:45.840
[Sighs]

29:45.880 --> 29:50.280
♪♪

29:50.320 --> 29:53.360
Maybe it's a good thing.

29:53.400 --> 29:56.240
Maybe she gets
her heartbreak...

29:56.280 --> 29:58.200
now rather than later.

30:02.040 --> 30:03.920
You know, they call it a crush
for a reason.

30:03.960 --> 30:07.120
-You're heartless.
-[Chuckles]

30:07.160 --> 30:08.280
[Ring clatters]

30:08.320 --> 30:09.560
And we,
more than anyone,

30:09.600 --> 30:13.440
need to be busting
the myth of "the one."

30:13.480 --> 30:16.600
We need to say there are
a million ones, infinite ones.

30:19.280 --> 30:22.160
Instead,
we fall into this --

30:22.200 --> 30:26.760
this Victorian,
archaic concept called marriage,

30:26.800 --> 30:28.440
which, quite frankly --
-Too many words.

30:28.480 --> 30:29.960
Quite frankly,
it was designed for a time

30:30.000 --> 30:31.960
when we all died by 40.

30:32.000 --> 30:36.200
Or we make a choice.
We choose.

30:36.240 --> 30:38.720
Like I chose you.

30:38.760 --> 30:41.680
[Tapping]

30:41.720 --> 30:44.480
[Clock ticking]

30:49.360 --> 30:50.840
You smell of wine.

30:59.360 --> 31:00.640
Look at today.

31:03.160 --> 31:05.200
Here's to Indiana Ray.

31:05.240 --> 31:08.280
[Glasses clink]

31:08.320 --> 31:11.040
Do they know how many more names
will be released?

31:11.080 --> 31:14.120
Another 50,000 tomorrow.

31:14.160 --> 31:15.640
Who knows after that.

31:15.680 --> 31:18.400
Some bishop blew his brains out
in Glasgow.

31:18.440 --> 31:20.560
Ohh.

31:20.600 --> 31:22.080
[Sighs]

31:22.120 --> 31:26.960
♪♪

31:27.000 --> 31:29.520
[Glass clinks]

31:29.560 --> 31:31.040
♪♪

31:31.080 --> 31:33.120
Hannah.

31:33.160 --> 31:39.880
♪♪

31:39.920 --> 31:41.040
[Cellphone ringing]

31:41.080 --> 31:43.360
It's...

31:43.400 --> 31:44.880
-Turn it off.
-Mm-hmm.

31:44.920 --> 31:46.160
[Ringing stops]

31:46.200 --> 31:47.880
[Cellphone thuds]

31:47.920 --> 31:54.960
♪♪

31:55.000 --> 32:02.080
♪♪

32:02.120 --> 32:10.120
♪♪

32:12.160 --> 32:14.760
[Birds chirping, dogs barking]

32:17.120 --> 32:18.160
[Toaster pops]

32:18.200 --> 32:19.960
Is that E.T.?

32:20.000 --> 32:22.120
What? That? What? No.

32:22.160 --> 32:24.000
E.T., phone home!

32:24.040 --> 32:25.480
Tilly: Shut up!

32:25.520 --> 32:27.040
E.T., go home!

32:27.080 --> 32:30.000
All right, you lot,
hurry up.

32:30.040 --> 32:32.160
Last one out's a biscuit.

32:32.200 --> 32:33.960
Biscuits?There's your coats,
got your noses...

32:34.000 --> 32:35.800
iPad!
[Door closes]

32:35.840 --> 32:38.320
[Birds chirping]

32:38.360 --> 32:43.920
♪♪

32:43.960 --> 32:45.640
Matthew: I'll need one hour
with the Foreign Secretary,

32:45.680 --> 32:47.320
and her husband
has to be there, too.

32:47.360 --> 32:49.160
All questions...
-To be pre-agreed?

32:49.200 --> 32:51.920
- [Laughs] Forget it.
-Matthew, come on.

32:51.960 --> 32:54.040
You're -- You're being given
exclusive access

32:54.080 --> 32:56.840
to a serving Foreign Secretary,
who will, on record,

32:56.880 --> 32:59.560
discuss her husband's liaisons
on an illicit website.

32:59.600 --> 33:01.360
In return, we will
need to be assured

33:01.400 --> 33:04.600
that the nature of those
liaisons are not disclosed.

33:04.640 --> 33:06.360
-[Sighs]
-What?

33:06.400 --> 33:09.120
You get the exclusive,
Matthew.

33:09.160 --> 33:11.000
It shuts the story down
for any of your rivals,

33:11.040 --> 33:13.880
and you get the headline
of the year.

33:13.920 --> 33:15.320
If she's going to do
this interview,

33:15.360 --> 33:17.880
it needs to happen today.

33:17.920 --> 33:19.560
Agreed.

33:19.600 --> 33:22.000
And there will be no mention
of any past indiscretions?

33:22.040 --> 33:24.200
No, the past
is another country.

33:24.240 --> 33:26.880
I won't go easy on them.

33:26.920 --> 33:29.920
They've got children.
And you're a good dad, Matthew.

33:29.960 --> 33:33.720
[Laughs] Yeah,
tell that to my ex-wife.

33:33.760 --> 33:35.520
We'll be in touch.

33:35.560 --> 33:36.880
Okay.
Thanks, Christie.

33:36.920 --> 33:38.840
[Line clicks]

33:38.880 --> 33:41.200
♪♪

33:41.240 --> 33:42.960
I didn't
fully walk you through

33:43.000 --> 33:45.960
what your divorce
will look like.

33:46.000 --> 33:48.360
You will stand up
in an open court

33:48.400 --> 33:50.080
if your husband
contests it,

33:50.120 --> 33:52.640
and your life will be
put on display --

33:52.680 --> 33:55.880
every detail designed
to shame you.

33:55.920 --> 33:59.200
The press will be waiting,
capturing your every move,

33:59.240 --> 34:02.440
ready to annihilate
you and your family.

34:02.480 --> 34:05.560
Every detail
of every relationship

34:05.600 --> 34:08.040
he has ever had
will be exposed.

34:10.120 --> 34:12.280
Including those
you may have tried to hide.

34:14.360 --> 34:16.160
You may not want to,

34:16.200 --> 34:21.960
but you will implicate
yourself and others.

34:22.000 --> 34:24.080
It will end your career.

34:24.120 --> 34:26.960
[Clock ticking]

34:27.000 --> 34:29.200
-Hannah --
-You lied to me by omission.

34:29.240 --> 34:32.880
Worse, you lied
on a sworn document.

34:34.760 --> 34:36.960
Do you know
what that means?

34:37.000 --> 34:38.280
Yes.

34:41.400 --> 34:43.240
Then how did you think
you could divorce

34:43.280 --> 34:46.440
and not expect that
to find you now,

34:46.480 --> 34:48.760
in the eye of the storm?
-I'm a politician.

34:48.800 --> 34:52.680
I'm always
in the eye of the storm.

34:52.720 --> 34:56.160
Noble & Hale have set up
a high-profile interview

34:56.200 --> 34:57.360
where you will be able

34:57.400 --> 34:59.360
to control your side
of the narrative

34:59.400 --> 35:01.120
before this story
and your life

35:01.160 --> 35:02.920
becomes fair game
for every tabloid out there.

35:02.960 --> 35:04.920
-Oh, Hannah --
-It is the only way

35:04.960 --> 35:08.360
you will be able to protect
your children from worse

35:08.400 --> 35:12.520
and come out
with some semblance of dignity.

35:12.560 --> 35:13.840
[Sighs]

35:13.880 --> 35:16.720
[Telephone ringing in distance]

35:20.960 --> 35:23.520
Mm. There are lies
you tell yourself.

35:25.760 --> 35:28.480
The small ones.

35:28.520 --> 35:31.560
"He's tired."
"You've had a long day."

35:31.600 --> 35:34.960
"You'll catch up
at the weekend."

35:35.000 --> 35:37.960
And then the weekend
never happens.

35:38.000 --> 35:42.320
And the weeks
turn into months, years.

35:42.360 --> 35:46.360
Until you roll over,
close your eyes,

35:46.400 --> 35:49.080
hope it will go away.

35:49.120 --> 35:50.360
[Sniffles]

35:50.400 --> 35:52.600
But it's always there.

35:56.080 --> 35:57.640
Why me?

35:57.680 --> 35:59.280
Why did you come to me?

36:01.240 --> 36:03.880
Your mother said to me

36:03.920 --> 36:05.920
if I was to ever
choose to divorce,

36:05.960 --> 36:09.080
then I was to go to you.

36:09.120 --> 36:12.040
And you'd do
the right thing.

36:12.080 --> 36:14.040
She said you always did.

36:16.440 --> 36:17.880
[Sighing] Oh.

36:19.840 --> 36:22.360
[Chuckles]

36:22.400 --> 36:23.720
What, she just
woke up this morning

36:23.760 --> 36:25.120
and decided
to stay with him?

36:25.160 --> 36:26.240
Yes. [Scoffs]

36:27.280 --> 36:28.840
[Sighs]

36:28.880 --> 36:30.400
What are you
not telling me?

36:32.000 --> 36:35.040
In case you need reminding,
you work for Noble & Hale.

36:35.080 --> 36:37.400
Zander, she's not
gone back to Defoe's.

36:41.200 --> 36:43.160
Politicians.

36:43.200 --> 36:44.680
You can never
trust them.

36:44.720 --> 36:45.720
Ah.

36:47.240 --> 36:48.240
[Sighs]

36:54.240 --> 36:57.080
Uh, it's -- Yeah.

36:57.120 --> 36:58.840
[Telephone ringing in distance]

36:58.880 --> 37:00.720
[Door closes]

37:00.760 --> 37:02.640
New list?

37:02.680 --> 37:03.800
Come on, hand over.

37:03.840 --> 37:05.040
It's not officially out

37:05.080 --> 37:07.160
until 7:00 a.m.
tomorrow morning.

37:07.200 --> 37:08.480
That's impressive.

37:08.520 --> 37:09.720
J.J. Johnson?

37:09.760 --> 37:12.600
Won't get it
for another five hours.

37:12.640 --> 37:14.920
What? We got Mr. Royston
an amazing interview.

37:14.960 --> 37:16.560
Quid pro quo.

37:16.600 --> 37:18.560
Unh, unh, unh. My assistant's
just printing out more.

37:18.600 --> 37:20.280
I'll make sure
there's one on your desk.

37:20.320 --> 37:24.320
You want to take a car or walk
to the Graham interview?

37:24.360 --> 37:26.800
You'll do a good job.
I need to be elsewhere.

37:31.240 --> 37:33.520
[Wheels rattling]

37:35.280 --> 37:36.720
-Nina.
-Oh, go away.

37:36.760 --> 37:38.760
I was drunk.

37:38.800 --> 37:41.440
You say things
when you're drunk,

37:41.480 --> 37:44.960
and the next morning
means nothing.

37:47.320 --> 37:49.200
Good to know.

37:49.240 --> 37:51.240
[Footsteps departing]

37:53.240 --> 37:55.720
[Cellphone ringing]

37:55.760 --> 37:58.600
[Sighs]

37:58.640 --> 37:59.840
Rose.

37:59.880 --> 38:02.560
Oh, God, give me
strength for tonight.

38:05.360 --> 38:07.000
Oh, mother of sod,
you forgot.

38:07.040 --> 38:09.720
-[Groans]
-Yeah, in some cultures,

38:09.760 --> 38:12.760
the entire family walks
the bride to the next village.

38:12.800 --> 38:15.320
You're getting married
in Kensal Rise.

38:18.680 --> 38:20.360
Say something funny.

38:20.400 --> 38:23.600
I put my hand
on the vicar's cock.

38:23.640 --> 38:25.680
[Laughs] What?

38:25.720 --> 38:28.040
Sorry.

38:28.080 --> 38:31.120
Uhh...
did it feel nice?

38:31.160 --> 38:32.440
-Okay.
-[Laughs]

38:32.480 --> 38:34.720
Okay, I'm hanging up
on you now!

38:39.840 --> 38:42.400
[Telephone ringing in distance]

38:45.880 --> 38:47.800
[Knock on door]

38:50.480 --> 38:52.080
Have you even eaten
today?

38:52.120 --> 38:53.440
[Chuckling] Oh.

38:53.480 --> 38:56.560
I think I had something
with cheese around 4:00.

38:56.600 --> 38:59.080
-You have to eat.
-[Chuckles]

38:59.120 --> 39:00.280
Donna.

39:02.560 --> 39:04.400
You have to talk
to the girls.

39:04.440 --> 39:06.120
[Sighs, sniffles]

39:06.160 --> 39:10.640
Then they'll hate me even more
than they do already.

39:10.680 --> 39:14.400
I hated mymother,
even when I loved her.

39:14.440 --> 39:17.520
Mm, thank you.
That's a great comfort.

39:17.560 --> 39:20.200
-Car'll be here in five.
-Okay.

39:22.720 --> 39:24.760
Danny DeVito and you
were up late last night.

39:24.800 --> 39:26.360
Simply going through
accounts.

39:26.400 --> 39:29.520
And I wish
you wouldn't call him that.

39:29.560 --> 39:30.840
Is everything all right?

39:30.880 --> 39:33.200
Yes, we were just having
a little overview.

39:33.240 --> 39:35.480
You know,
shifting things about.

39:35.520 --> 39:38.440
Yes, yes, fine.

39:38.480 --> 39:41.040
Car's here.

39:41.080 --> 39:44.840
[Telephone ringing in distance]

39:44.880 --> 39:48.240
What's going on, Donna?
Which accounts are those?

39:48.280 --> 39:51.320
-Have a good night.
-Yeah. Right.

39:53.920 --> 39:55.240
[Keys jangle, lock clicks]

39:55.280 --> 39:57.480
Bill: [Laughs]
I'll bring Mrs. Graham out.

39:57.520 --> 39:59.200
Thank you very much.

39:59.240 --> 40:03.040
[Indistinct talking]

40:03.080 --> 40:05.840
You look beautiful,
darling.

40:05.880 --> 40:08.480
Thank you.

40:08.520 --> 40:10.040
You won't regret this.

40:12.280 --> 40:14.480
I've got him
onto fly fishing.

40:14.520 --> 40:18.000
We might do the odd
extra question on it.

40:18.040 --> 40:19.440
Clever you.

40:23.440 --> 40:26.160
[Indistinct talking]

40:31.040 --> 40:32.680
[Exhales sharply]

40:36.600 --> 40:37.720
You okay?

40:40.040 --> 40:42.600
I'm a state schoolgirl
from Manchester

40:42.640 --> 40:44.600
at the height
of my career.

40:44.640 --> 40:48.400
The work it has
taken me to get here.

40:52.040 --> 40:54.200
It's not without love,
our marriage.

40:56.480 --> 40:59.880
But I am married to a man
whose particular predilection,

40:59.920 --> 41:02.440
I just can't satisfy.

41:08.280 --> 41:09.920
I'm not used to failing.

41:12.200 --> 41:14.280
I don't see divorce
as failure.

41:14.320 --> 41:17.480
I just see some marriages
as finite.

41:17.520 --> 41:18.560
Mm.

41:18.600 --> 41:20.120
♪♪

41:20.160 --> 41:23.600
When you are
out of office...

41:23.640 --> 41:26.360
♪♪

41:26.400 --> 41:29.000
...when you are away
from the spotlight,

41:29.040 --> 41:32.920
and all three boys
have left home,

41:32.960 --> 41:35.560
when none of this
matters anymore...

41:35.600 --> 41:38.280
We make a break
for the border?

41:38.320 --> 41:41.080
♪♪

41:41.120 --> 41:44.000
Discreetly. Quietly.

41:44.040 --> 41:46.160
Ramsey: Emma. He wants
to start the interview.

41:46.200 --> 41:48.400
Away from the glare.

41:48.440 --> 41:57.760
♪♪

41:57.800 --> 41:59.800
[Emma clears throat]

41:59.840 --> 42:03.760
♪♪

42:03.800 --> 42:06.120
[Wheels rattling]

42:06.160 --> 42:10.040
♪♪

42:10.080 --> 42:12.120
[Door opens]

42:12.160 --> 42:13.960
♪♪

42:14.000 --> 42:16.960
[Indistinct conversation]

42:17.000 --> 42:23.320
♪♪

42:23.360 --> 42:24.600
I called your office.

42:24.640 --> 42:26.320
The case I'm on
is the bitch from hell.

42:26.360 --> 42:27.960
Final hearing, and we didn't
have half the paperwork.

42:28.000 --> 42:31.280
I was gonna call you.
I have a good lead on the --

42:31.320 --> 42:34.640
♪♪

42:34.680 --> 42:36.400
We got it early.

42:39.800 --> 42:42.920
Officially, you've got
12 hours' grace.

42:42.960 --> 42:45.960
Unofficially, uh...

42:46.000 --> 42:49.120
Unless it's
a different Stern?

42:49.160 --> 42:50.960
You told Hannah?

42:51.000 --> 42:52.880
No.

42:52.920 --> 42:54.400
But by the end
of play today,

42:54.440 --> 42:56.920
every paralegal in town
will be poring over it.

42:56.960 --> 43:01.920
♪♪

43:01.960 --> 43:03.640
Tell her.

43:03.680 --> 43:05.480
Before she hears about it
from someone else.

43:05.520 --> 43:12.360
♪♪

43:12.400 --> 43:14.920
[Rain pattering]

43:14.960 --> 43:19.360
♪♪

43:19.400 --> 43:21.000
You wrote
my dissertation.

43:21.040 --> 43:22.160
No.

43:23.360 --> 43:24.480
Did I?

43:27.120 --> 43:28.200
I did.

43:33.280 --> 43:34.760
Fine.

43:34.800 --> 43:36.080
We're quits.

43:41.240 --> 43:42.640
I want to not
have to do this.

43:42.680 --> 43:44.480
When can I stop
doing this?

43:46.520 --> 43:49.960
Clearing up
my family's mess?

43:50.000 --> 43:51.360
I left Defoe's.

43:51.400 --> 43:54.120
No.
You changed your name.

43:54.160 --> 43:56.280
That's something different.

43:56.320 --> 44:02.280
♪♪

44:02.320 --> 44:08.280
♪♪

44:08.320 --> 44:10.040
[Wind blowing]

44:10.080 --> 44:12.640
[Siren wailing in distance]

44:12.680 --> 44:15.360
♪♪

44:15.400 --> 44:16.960
-Hey.
-[Screams] Jesus.

44:17.000 --> 44:18.560
Sorry. Sorry.

44:18.600 --> 44:21.400
-Were you hiding?
-That obvious?

44:21.440 --> 44:23.640
I keep saying
we need more light!

44:23.680 --> 44:26.080
They're all inside.
I'm the vicar -- Glen.

44:26.120 --> 44:27.680
I'm the sister --
Hannah.

44:27.720 --> 44:30.040
Hi.

44:30.080 --> 44:33.360
And peonies all the way
down either side.

44:33.400 --> 44:36.000
Lovely.Do we even know
what peonies are?

44:36.040 --> 44:37.080
-Not a clue.
-Oh.

44:37.120 --> 44:39.160
Ruth!
I've changed to wearing red,

44:39.200 --> 44:40.840
just to give you
the heads-up.

44:40.880 --> 44:43.560
It's quite bright, so it's
probably best not to compete,

44:43.600 --> 44:45.360
and I wouldn't want you
to look washed out.

44:45.400 --> 44:46.720
I don't think
we'll have that problem.

44:46.760 --> 44:49.280
Hannah: Sorry! Sorry.

44:49.320 --> 44:50.640
Oh, good.

44:50.680 --> 44:53.320
Did the nice vicar...
rescue you?

44:53.360 --> 44:57.960
Wow, it's, uh...
definitely a church.

44:58.000 --> 44:59.240
-Hi. Nice to meet you.
Oh, hello.

44:59.280 --> 45:01.000
Nathan,
Hannah's husband.

45:01.040 --> 45:06.520
Uh, we're gonna ask everyone
to walk from here to the house.

45:06.560 --> 45:08.800
Uh, Nathan?

45:08.840 --> 45:10.760
You're in charge of ushers,
so keep them in line.

45:10.800 --> 45:12.880
-Yes, milady.
-Coming into the church,

45:12.920 --> 45:15.360
groom will be waiting
that side,

45:15.400 --> 45:18.400
then me, the bride, this side.[Door opens, closes]

45:18.440 --> 45:22.440
Hannah, Nina,
you'll be behind me.

45:25.520 --> 45:28.480
And Dad will walk me
down to here.

45:28.520 --> 45:29.960
Dad's walking you
down the aisle?

45:30.000 --> 45:30.960
Yeah.

45:33.120 --> 45:35.920
Oscar: Ah.
This must be Annie.

45:35.960 --> 45:37.200
Annie: Hello.

45:37.240 --> 45:39.800
-And -- ah. Miles.
-Welcome.

45:42.600 --> 45:45.440
Look at it. Look at it.
Hasn't changed a bit.

45:45.480 --> 45:47.040
Nope.

45:47.080 --> 45:50.640
-It's beautiful.
-They were married here.

45:50.680 --> 45:52.960
The frescoes
have faded.

45:53.000 --> 45:54.280
Like everything.

45:54.320 --> 45:56.480
Oh, church
makes you so morbid.

45:56.520 --> 45:58.400
Why must you
be so morbid?

46:00.080 --> 46:01.760
-Uh, where do I stand?
-Oh, umm...

46:01.800 --> 46:03.960
[Indistinct conversation]

46:04.000 --> 46:05.960
It's the biggest day
of your life.

46:06.000 --> 46:08.080
♪♪

46:08.120 --> 46:10.520
[Indistinct conversation]

46:10.560 --> 46:15.720
♪♪

46:15.760 --> 46:20.960
♪♪

46:21.000 --> 46:23.000
[Door opens]

46:23.040 --> 46:30.200
♪♪

46:30.240 --> 46:34.040
No, 'cause at the moment,
we've got 140.

46:34.080 --> 46:36.280
I -- I think we want
to keep it small.

46:36.320 --> 46:39.160
I know, darling, but as you
only get to do it once.

46:39.200 --> 46:40.280
Hopefully.

46:40.320 --> 46:43.000
Nina, now,
who are you bringing?

46:43.040 --> 46:44.160
More wine.

46:45.880 --> 46:48.840
Incidentally, Ruth, we were
wondering about your check.

46:48.880 --> 46:51.520
Um [Chuckles] it's just the
caterer's getting a bit antsy.

46:51.560 --> 46:53.160
That's all.

46:53.200 --> 46:55.680
We had over 300
at our wedding.

46:55.720 --> 46:57.880
I don't remember
any of them.

46:57.920 --> 47:00.560
I'm certainly not in contact
with any of them.

47:00.600 --> 47:04.600
It was hot and cramped,
and my dress was too tight.

47:04.640 --> 47:06.320
But it was such fun.

47:08.440 --> 47:11.520
Yes. It was, wasn't it?[Liquid pouring]

47:14.040 --> 47:16.120
[Indistinct conversation]

47:19.360 --> 47:21.600
[Siren wailing in distance]

47:21.640 --> 47:24.120
[Indistinct conversation]

47:27.600 --> 47:29.880
Why am I seeing
roller skates?

47:32.000 --> 47:35.400
Roller disco.
My ninth birthday.

47:35.440 --> 47:38.640
-Didn't we, um --
-Roll back the carpets.

47:38.680 --> 47:40.680
I broke in my new skates
on this floor.

47:40.720 --> 47:41.960
[Chuckling]
Yes, of course.

47:42.000 --> 47:43.600
I have a photo
of that day somewhere.

47:43.640 --> 47:46.440
Didn't I send it to you?
-Mm.

47:46.480 --> 47:47.960
You sent him things?

47:48.000 --> 47:50.880
Yeah,
in the beginning, yeah.

47:50.920 --> 47:52.760
For a while.

47:52.800 --> 47:55.800
We have a -- a beautiful photo
of you and Nathan

47:55.840 --> 47:58.760
at your wedding
on our mantelpiece.

47:58.800 --> 47:59.760
Ah.

47:59.800 --> 48:02.040
When Vinnie was born,

48:02.080 --> 48:03.960
I knew
that would be important.

48:04.000 --> 48:06.800
Finally,
the Defoes had a boy.

48:06.840 --> 48:10.240
[Dishes clanking in distance]

48:10.280 --> 48:13.680
Glen: The real act of marriage
is in the heart.

48:13.720 --> 48:15.440
[Laughs]

48:15.480 --> 48:17.680
But you might as well fill up
the church while you're at it?

48:17.720 --> 48:20.120
[Laughs]Well, the church isn't
paying for it, so --

48:20.160 --> 48:22.520
-Behave.
-Don't worry about that now.

48:22.560 --> 48:23.800
No?

48:23.840 --> 48:27.120
We -- We almost
missed our wedding.

48:27.160 --> 48:31.200
Hannah was --
Hannah was late, and, uh, I --

48:31.240 --> 48:33.600
[Chuckling] I got stuck in
the loo at the registry office.

48:33.640 --> 48:34.960
[Laughter]

48:35.000 --> 48:38.320
But, um,
when she did arrive,

48:38.360 --> 48:42.560
she looked so...

48:42.600 --> 48:45.160
red from running.

48:45.200 --> 48:46.240
[Laughter]

48:46.280 --> 48:47.920
Even so...

48:47.960 --> 48:49.880
It's a five-minute warning
'cause we should...

48:51.600 --> 48:54.000
Ah. And he pours
more wine.

48:54.040 --> 48:58.720
Even so, it was
the best day of my life.

48:58.760 --> 49:00.640
Annie: Aww.

49:00.680 --> 49:02.800
-[Scoffs]
-Now, what about speeches?

49:02.840 --> 49:05.000
Yes -- speeches.

49:05.040 --> 49:08.160
Well, it's usually groom,
best man, father of the bride.

49:08.200 --> 49:10.160
Although I know Dad doesn't mind
saying a few words.

49:10.200 --> 49:12.240
I'm very happy to do it.

49:12.280 --> 49:14.800
Mm. Um, well,
I think Ruth was going --

49:14.840 --> 49:17.840
-Well...
-If you'd like to, Dad.

49:17.880 --> 49:19.320
-Mum's doing it.
-No, it --

49:19.360 --> 49:21.080
-It should be Mum who does it.
-No, Nina.

49:21.120 --> 49:22.440
Well, she hasn't
written anything yet, so --

49:22.480 --> 49:23.880
Well, give her a chance.

49:23.920 --> 49:25.760
Or do you want to take
that job, too, Dad?

49:25.800 --> 49:28.360
-I --
-She's been busy. Weren't you?

49:28.400 --> 49:30.040
-Uh, yes.
-And what will you say, Mother?

49:30.080 --> 49:32.040
What will you share
on that wonderful institution

49:32.080 --> 49:33.560
that is marriage?[Laughter]

